French artist Arnaud d'Hauterives' painting Daughter of Fire on display at the National Art Museum of China Photo: Courtesy of the National Art Museum of ChinaA new exhibition featuring a collection of artists from France's Académie des Beaux-Arts is highlighting French art at the National Art Museum of China (NAMOC). The Immortal Heritage show includes a selection of 118 artworks from the NAMOC's collection of 163 French works covering oil paintings, Chinese-style paintings, prints and installation works. According to Wu Weishan, president of the museum, the exhibition is an important showcase of French art in China as well as the cultural exchanges between China and France. During the first half of the 20th century, a number of young Chinese such as artist Xu Beihong went to France to study art. Some of them, including Zhao Wuji and Xiong Bingming chose to stay in France to pursue styles that fused Chinese and French art traditions.  The exhibition will end Sunday. 
